            <br>
            <p>
                <h3 class="subtitle">SECTION 1 - POLICY AVAILABILITY</h3>

                Our policy is not available for goods you have received from the seller in a face to face manner, or delivered by himself. The seller can have his own return policy, which will be subjected to laws accordingly.
            </p>
            <br>
            <p>
                <h3 class="subtitle">SECTION 2 - CONDITIONS</h3>
                <p>
                    If a buyer hasn't confirmed receiving the item after 21 days of the seller confirming delivery and providing proof of it, the transaction will be closed and the seller will receive the amount owed for the product. 
                </p>
                <p>
                    To be eligible for a return, your item must be unused and in the same condition that you received it. It must also be in the original packaging.
                </p>
                <p>
                    If we have provided shipping for the specific sale, the buyer has 14 days to request a refund.
                </p>
            </p>
            <br>
            <p>
                <h3 class="subtitle">SECTION 3 - PROOF</h3>
                The buyer must provide proof of the damaged, wrong, etc. product in their refund request, to help with their case in case of a dispute.
            </p>
            <br>
            <p>
                <h3 class="subtitle">SECTION 4 - OBLIGATIONS</h3>

                <p>
                    The seller can choose whether or not to refund the purchase. In case they decline or don't respond within 7 days, a dispute will be created. 
                </p>
                <p>
                    Both the buyer and the seller will send information regarding their stance and the dispute will be solved by a staff member. 
                </p>
                <p>
                    If the buyer's refund request is accepted, then they must send the product back to the seller. If the seller hasn't confirmed receiving the item after 21 days of the buyer confirming delivery and providing proof of it, the transaction will be closed and the buyer will receive the amount owed.
                </p>
            </p>
            <br>
            <p>
                <h3 class="subtitle">SECTION 5 - RETURNS</h3>
                <p>
                    To return your product, you should send it to the original seller's address, or the one discussed with him.
                </p>
                <p>
                    You will be responsible for paying for your own shipping costs for returning your item. Shipping costs are non-refundable. If you receive a refund, the cost of return shipping will be deducted from your refund.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Depending on where you live, the time it may take for your returned product to get back to the seller, may vary.
                </p>
            </p>
            <br>
            <p>
                <h3 class="subtitle">SECTION 6 - PROBLEMS</h3>

                <ol>
                    <li>How to open a dispute:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Sellers want to maintain a good reputation and in most cases will look to fix the problem straightaway, so contact them first.</li>
                            <li>Once you submit a refund request, a dispute will be automatically opened if the seller declines your request or doesn't reply in a week.</li>
                            <li>After the dispute is open, a staff member of Deal Your Crypto will resolve it as soon as possible.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Having trouble with the refund request?
                        <ul>
                            <li>The seller has 7 days to get back to you. You can respond to the seller via the chat from the deal you opened a dispute for.</li>
                            <li>You can close the dispute after the seller resolved the issue to your satisfaction. If we haven't heard from you in 21 days, the dispute will be automatically closed.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Deal Your Crypto handles the dispute
                        <ul>
                            <li>We'll review the information provided by both parties and get back to you as soon as possible.</li>
                            <li>The disputes are available for all products sent usually by post. Such exceptions are: vehicles, real estate, business for sale, digital goods or services.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
